G04 EDITING NOTES START*
G04 Units are millimeters. FSLAX35Y35 means 100000 coordinate units per mm*
G04 Table origin is X2.0 Y2.0 mm. Cell size is 24.0 x 15.0 mm*
G04 Table layout is 4 columns by 4 rows, filled from top-left to bottom-right*
G04 Search marker format: CELL NN BEGIN NAME and CELL NN END NAME*
G04 Font glyph aperture blocks are D100-D135: A-Z then 0-9*
G04 Labels are flashed with the glyph blocks and temporarily scaled by LS*
G04 Drawing apertures are D10-D30; D30 is C with a round hole*
G04 D140 marked star, D142 plain star, D143 AB clearing stack*
G04 D150 nested shape 1, D151 nested shape 2, D152 nested assembly*
G04 Aperture macro test apertures: D141 SMILE and D153 HOLESTACK*
G04 Cell order: G01 LINE, G02 ARC, G03 ARC, APERTURE*
G04 Cell order: REGION, AB CLEARING, AB BLOCK, MACRO*
G04 Cell order: ROTATION, MIRROR, SCALE, COMBO*
G04 Cell order: AB NESTED, MACRO HOLE STACK, AP HOLE*
G04 EDITING NOTES END*
